<?xml version='1.0'?>
<!DOCTYPE book PUBLIC "-//OASIS//DTD DocBook XML V4.5//EN" 
    "http://www.oasis-open.org/docbook/xml/4.5/docbookx.dtd">
<book id="javaee-intro">
    <bookinfo>
        <title>Java Enterprise Edition (JavaEE) Intro</title>
        <subtitle>version 6</subtitle>
        <issuenum>${content.version}</issuenum>
        <pubdate>${docbook.pubdate}</pubdate>
        <copyright>
            <year>${copyright.year}</year>
            <holder>${copyright.holder}</holder>
        </copyright>
        <abstract>
            <para>
                This presentation introduces the JavaEE enterprise framework and
                its associated API standards.
            </para>
        </abstract>
    </bookinfo>

    <preface id="javaeeintro-purpose">
        <title>Purpose</title>
        <itemizedlist spacing="compact">
            <listitem><para>Become familiar with JavaEE architectures</para>
                <itemizedlist spacing="compact">
                    <listitem><para>Understand the purpose of Java SE, Java ME, and Java EE</para></listitem>
                    <listitem><para>Understand the purpose of key Java EE APIs</para></listitem>
                    <listitem><para>Understand the purpose of the JavaEE container/application server</para></listitem>
                </itemizedlist>
            </listitem>
            <listitem><para>Understand the difference between the API and the provider</para></listitem>
            <listitem><para>Understand there are significant variations of JavaEE architectures</para></listitem>
        </itemizedlist>
    </preface>

    <xi:include href="javaee-intro-why.xml" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" />
    <xi:include href="javaee-intro-java-levels.xml" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" />
    <xi:include href="javaee-intro-javaee-arch.xml" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" />
    <xi:include href="javaee-intro-javaee-versions.xml" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" />
    <xi:include href="javaee-intro-javaee-specs.xml" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" />
    <xi:include href="javaee-intro-ejb.xml" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" />

    <chapter id="javaeeintro-summary">
        <title>Summary</title>
        <itemizedlist>
            <listitem><para>Made a technical case for JavaEE and EJB</para></listitem>
            <listitem><para>Described an envolution of EJB</para></listitem>
            <listitem><para>Showed where EJB fits within the JavaEE Specs</para></listitem>
            <listitem><para>Introduced 4-5 types of EJBs</para></listitem>
            <listitem><para>Introduced 3 EJB deployment types</para></listitem>
        </itemizedlist>
	</chapter>
    
